    "comment": "Rationale: Using immuno electron microscopy, it is demonstrated that RIBEYE is specifically located in the ribbon of the ribbon synapse.. Experimental description: Immunogold electron microscopy was performed largely as previously described (Schmitz and Drenckhahn 1993). Bovine retina fixed with 2% freshly depolymerized paraformaldehyde, 0.1% glutaraldehyde in PBS for 3 hr at 4°C were washed with PBS (six times, each for 10 min) and infiltrated with 0.5% tannic acid (Mallinckrodt) in PBS (1 hr at 4°C).",
